WEBVTT

00:01.376 --> 00:02.711
<i>Previously on</i> This Is Us...

00:02.794 --> 00:04.295
OFFICIANT:
You may now kiss the bride.

00:05.338 --> 00:06.464
<i>BETH:</i>
<i>"I would never</i>

00:06.548 --> 00:09.467
leave you lost."
In female handwriting.

00:09.551 --> 00:11.344
This a love letter?

00:11.428 --> 00:13.179
Look, a bra.

00:13.263 --> 00:15.306
BETH:
And it's right next to some kind
of floral wrap thingy.

00:15.390 --> 00:18.143
Who do you think
he slept with last night?

00:19.144 --> 00:22.439
MADISON: It could be the
wedding singer. Philip's friend.

00:22.522 --> 00:24.107
-She was
at the rehearsal last night.
-Mm-hmm.

00:24.190 --> 00:26.401
And they were talking.

00:26.484 --> 00:28.486
-(Randall speaking indistinctly)
-MADISON: (gasps) Wait.

00:28.570 --> 00:31.281
Did you see that look
Sophie just gave him?

00:31.364 --> 00:33.533
-They have
crazy history together.
-Mm-hmm.

00:33.616 --> 00:35.368
MADISON:
But wait. She's married.

00:35.452 --> 00:37.871
-Oh, yeah. That's not her MO.
-Mm. No.

00:37.954 --> 00:40.457
-BETH: Then there's Cassidy,
his plus-one.
-MADISON: Right.

00:40.540 --> 00:42.167
Just as a friend, though.

00:42.250 --> 00:44.002
<i>RANDALL:</i>
<i>So, for real, bro,</i>

00:44.085 --> 00:46.087
what happened
with you last night?

00:46.171 --> 00:48.465
Oh, man, it's a long story.

00:48.548 --> 00:50.300
Is it a good story?

00:51.343 --> 00:53.178
(exhales)

00:54.512 --> 00:57.140
♪ ♪

01:25.960 --> 01:31.132
-ARIELLE: ♪ <i>Wise men say...</i> ♪
-(indistinct chatter)

01:32.967 --> 01:35.637
What time it is.
You guys have the time?

01:35.720 --> 01:37.555
Uh, we're about to have
our rehearsal dinner.

01:37.639 --> 01:40.266
-Do you have somewhere else
to be? I don't...
-KEVIN: No.

01:40.350 --> 01:43.353
No, that's not what I was...
talking about at all.

01:43.436 --> 01:44.562
KATE:
Mm-hmm.

01:44.646 --> 01:47.607
She's really something, huh?

01:47.691 --> 01:50.360
-♪ <i>Falling in love...</i> ♪
-(Kate sighs)

01:50.443 --> 01:52.195
Pearson kryptonite.
Hot singers onstage

01:52.278 --> 01:53.571
singing rock classics.

01:53.655 --> 01:56.700
-It's how Dad fell for Mom.
-Yeah.

01:56.783 --> 01:59.953
Oh, uh, "Moonshadow," right?

02:00.036 --> 02:01.162
-Wow.
-KATE: Mm-hmm.

02:01.246 --> 02:02.956
I had to brush up
on my Pearson trivia

02:03.039 --> 02:05.500
before, you know, marrying one.

02:05.583 --> 02:07.168
-KATE: Mm.
-Aw.

02:07.252 --> 02:09.587
-(Philip chuckles)
-KATE: Let's go say hi
to somebody else.

02:09.671 --> 02:11.256
-All right, have fun.
-KATE: Okay.

02:13.466 --> 02:18.138
♪ <i>So, take my hand...</i> ♪

02:18.221 --> 02:20.974
-Looking good, Pearson.
-Oh, thank you very, very much.

02:21.057 --> 02:22.434
You're not looking so bad
yourself.

02:22.517 --> 02:24.227
I'm wearing makeup.
I can't wait to wash my face.

02:24.310 --> 02:25.979
But also, yeah, I know.

02:26.062 --> 02:28.106
-You know. (laughs)
-I do.

02:28.189 --> 02:29.649
♪ <i>But I...</i> ♪

02:29.733 --> 02:32.986
-Manny say "slut." (laughs)
-Well, hey.

02:33.069 --> 02:34.988
Haven't heard that one before.
Hi.

02:35.071 --> 02:37.490
-Oliver. Philip's cousin.
-Kevin.

02:37.574 --> 02:40.535
Oh. So, I, uh, hear you and I

02:40.618 --> 02:43.204
are the only eligible blokes
at this shindig.

02:43.288 --> 02:45.582
Any thoughts
on who you want to go for?

02:45.665 --> 02:47.876
I-I don't want
to step on any toes

02:47.959 --> 02:49.294
or cross any swords.

02:49.377 --> 02:50.879
U-Unless you're into that.

02:50.962 --> 02:52.922
No. I... You know, I was...
I was actually just here

02:53.006 --> 02:55.050
to celebrate
with Kate and Philip, so...

02:55.133 --> 02:56.718
Okay.

02:56.801 --> 02:57.802
(chuckles)

02:57.886 --> 03:00.055
Okay. Easy. Easy.

03:00.138 --> 03:02.974
Yeah, you got it. Pace yourself.

03:04.017 --> 03:06.478
-Oliver. Yeah.
-RANDALL: Hmm.

03:07.479 --> 03:08.605
What?

03:08.688 --> 03:09.939
Come on, man.

03:10.023 --> 03:11.608
We both know you've been staring

03:11.691 --> 03:14.861
at that door, willing Sophie
to walk through it all day.

03:14.944 --> 03:16.529
No, I don't even know
what you're talking about.

03:16.613 --> 03:18.281
-I have not been doing
any of those things.
-RANDALL: Mm-hmm.

03:18.365 --> 03:20.367
How many times have you seen her
in the last few years?

03:20.450 --> 03:22.744
Just twice. You know, I saw her
once at her mother's funeral,

03:22.827 --> 03:26.623
and then I saw her again at Kate
and Philip's engagement party.

03:26.706 --> 03:28.625
She's a married woman, Kev.

03:28.708 --> 03:31.711
Don't cause any drama
at our sister's wedding.

03:31.795 --> 03:34.756
Look, Sophie and I are cool.
All right, man?

03:34.839 --> 03:36.800
We're...

03:41.054 --> 03:43.056
Nothing to worry about.

03:45.642 --> 03:46.810
RANDALL:
Right.

03:46.893 --> 03:50.980
♪ <i>Can't help</i> ♪

03:51.064 --> 03:54.984
♪ <i>Falling in love</i> ♪

03:55.068 --> 04:00.740
♪ <i>With you.</i> ♪

04:00.824 --> 04:02.992
REBECCA:
Sophie, it's so good to see you.

04:03.076 --> 04:04.994
You must be so tired.

04:05.078 --> 04:07.163
Oh, my gosh, I must look it.
I just had

04:07.247 --> 04:10.417
-a really,
really long plane ride.
-How's college?

04:10.500 --> 04:11.710
How are you and Kevin

04:11.793 --> 04:13.962
handling the long distance?

04:14.045 --> 04:17.257
Oh. Um... It's,

04:17.340 --> 04:19.801
-uh...
-REBECCA: Yeah,
I-I know it's rough,

04:19.884 --> 04:21.261
but hang in there.

04:21.344 --> 04:22.762
Yeah.

04:22.846 --> 04:25.265
Well, it's-it's really wonderful
to see you again.

04:25.348 --> 04:27.017
REBECCA:
Mm. It's good to see you,

04:27.100 --> 04:28.935
-too.
-SOPHIE: Yeah.

04:30.603 --> 04:32.439
(Sophie chuckles softly)

04:32.522 --> 04:34.065
-Hey.
-Hey.

04:34.149 --> 04:35.442
I'm just so sorry
about all this,

04:35.525 --> 04:36.693
um, but I'm Arielle,

04:36.776 --> 04:38.403
and I'm gonna give you
a big hug right now.

04:38.486 --> 04:40.530
-Oh. Yeah, okay.
-Okay.

04:40.613 --> 04:42.741
Can you see the man behind me?

04:43.742 --> 04:46.161
Oh, yeah.
That's, uh, that's Oliver.

04:46.244 --> 04:48.663
-Is he still there?
-He is still there.

04:48.747 --> 04:49.914
-I'm so sorry.
-Yeah.

04:49.998 --> 04:52.125
I-I've just been meaning
to tell you,

04:52.208 --> 04:54.502
I am your biggest fan!

04:54.586 --> 04:56.588
I mean, that season finale?

04:56.671 --> 04:59.007
I mean, I didn't know

04:59.090 --> 05:00.967
-a sitcom could be
so heartwarming!
-KEVIN: Well,

05:01.051 --> 05:03.219
-thank you very,
very much. Um...
-(chuckles) Yeah.

05:04.262 --> 05:06.014
Hugh Grant's opposite
has-has left. I think

05:06.097 --> 05:07.849
-the coast is clear.
-(sighs) Thank you.

05:07.932 --> 05:09.642
Yeah, no problem.
Anything for a fan.

05:09.726 --> 05:11.019
Oh.

05:11.102 --> 05:13.938
Actually,
I've never seen your show.

05:14.022 --> 05:16.649
-Yeah. Yeah.
-(chuckles) I'm just more
of a podcast person.

05:16.733 --> 05:18.360
No, honestly, I couldn't be
less offended, really.

05:18.443 --> 05:20.403
That's, uh... It's... You know,

05:20.487 --> 05:22.322
I'm-I'm gonna go talk
to an old friend real quick.

05:22.405 --> 05:24.741
-Of course. Mm-hmm.
-Okay? It was good
talking to you.

05:24.824 --> 05:27.243
-(chuckles): You, too. Okay.
-Okay, I'll see you. All right.

05:29.204 --> 05:31.873
-Dad! Dad! Dad! Dad!
-Ah! Hey! Ah, there you are.
(babbles)

05:31.956 --> 05:33.625
-What do we got? What do we got?
-Can we go make s'mores

05:33.708 --> 05:35.835
-at the bonfire?
-Can we? Can we, please?

05:35.919 --> 05:39.047
Uh, this is a lot of sugar.
What'd your mom say?

05:39.130 --> 05:41.508
She said it's fine as long as
you get the stuff to make them.

05:41.591 --> 05:44.844
-As long as I get the stuff
to make them.
-If it's not too much trouble.

05:44.928 --> 05:46.638
No. No, I don't think it's
too much trouble. S'mores it is.

05:46.721 --> 05:48.223
-All right? Yeah?
-MADISON: (gasps) Yeah!
-(kids cheer)

05:48.306 --> 05:49.849
You get s'mores.

05:49.933 --> 05:51.601
Oh, we better get a jacket.

05:51.685 --> 05:52.686
-KEVIN: Yeah.
-MADISON: It's gonna be cold.

05:55.188 --> 05:56.773
Are you sure this isn't yours?

05:56.856 --> 05:59.150
(chuckles):
No, this-this is not my luggage.

05:59.234 --> 06:01.444
Trust me, if this was my bag,
I would know.

06:01.528 --> 06:03.738
Well, if I were you, I might
just pretend it's mine to see

06:03.822 --> 06:05.115
what the heck
is inside this thing.

06:05.198 --> 06:08.410
-So, <i>are</i> you sure?
-Yes.
-Ma'am?

06:08.493 --> 06:10.370
(chuckles): Are you sure
that's not your bag?

06:10.453 --> 06:12.622
(chuckles)

06:12.706 --> 06:15.208
Uh, so, what-what happened?
The airport lose

06:15.291 --> 06:16.626
-your luggage?
-Yep.

06:16.710 --> 06:18.545
Now I'm totally screwed 'cause,

06:18.628 --> 06:20.046
you know, I just have

06:20.130 --> 06:22.132
this emergency pair of underwear
'cause you never want

06:22.215 --> 06:24.759
-to get stuck in an ER
with dirty drawers.
-Stuck at the ER.

06:24.843 --> 06:27.220
-That's your mom's number one...
-That's my mom's only... Yeah.

06:27.303 --> 06:29.597
...rule. Yeah.

06:32.851 --> 06:35.979
-(Sophie clears throat)
-Uh, okay, so, what do we do?
How do I fix this?

06:36.062 --> 06:38.231
-How do we get you clothes?
-Most of the stores in town

06:38.314 --> 06:39.274
close in half an hour.

06:39.357 --> 06:41.109
Things shut down early here.

06:41.192 --> 06:44.195
-You and Grant rent a car?
-Oh, no.

06:44.279 --> 06:46.406
No, he, uh, he actually
got stuck in New York.

06:46.489 --> 06:49.117
It's a long, boring story.

06:49.200 --> 06:51.119
-Just had to work.
-Um, I could drive you.

06:51.202 --> 06:53.204
-Oh, you don't have to.
-It's okay.

06:53.288 --> 06:54.664
I got to run into town
and grab some stuff anyway.

06:54.748 --> 06:55.790
I'll-I'll drive you.

06:55.874 --> 06:57.250
-Really? Are you sure?
-Yeah.

06:57.334 --> 06:59.502
Yeah. It's not a problem.

06:59.586 --> 07:01.588
-Okay.
-Okay. Can you
pull the car around?

07:01.671 --> 07:03.882
-Of course, right away.
-Yeah? All right, come on.

07:03.965 --> 07:05.967
(vehicle approaching)

07:14.934 --> 07:16.519
I rented it for Kate and Philip.

07:16.603 --> 07:17.771
So, it's either this

07:17.854 --> 07:19.481
-or a golf cart.
-(Sophie chuckles)

07:19.564 --> 07:20.940
SOPHIE:
Okay.

07:21.983 --> 07:23.109
Shall we?

07:24.152 --> 07:26.363
(car door opens)

07:32.077 --> 07:34.245
Uh...

07:34.329 --> 07:36.331
Just, uh... This is a lot,

07:36.414 --> 07:38.458
-right?
-Yeah, that's probably
a good call.

07:38.541 --> 07:39.959
-Yeah. Here you go.
-(car door closes)

07:40.043 --> 07:42.420
Okay. All right.

07:55.725 --> 07:57.519
(exhales)
Sorry, Soph.

07:57.602 --> 07:59.354
Looks like this was
our last option.

07:59.437 --> 08:01.398
SOPHIE:
Hmm.

08:04.609 --> 08:06.611
I think I have an idea.

08:15.662 --> 08:17.622
-Hi there.
-Hi.

08:17.706 --> 08:20.041
-SOPHIE: Hey.
-Just about to close.

08:20.125 --> 08:21.459
I'm sorry,
you don't happen to have

08:21.543 --> 08:23.586
a rack of unclaimed clothes,
do you?

08:23.670 --> 08:25.964
-(exhales)
-Look, I-I'm in town
for a wedding,

08:26.047 --> 08:28.842
and the airport lost my luggage.
(chuckles)

08:28.925 --> 08:31.052
I just...
I'm really in a bind here.

08:32.512 --> 08:33.888
(sighs)

08:36.224 --> 08:38.059
Watch your head.

08:38.143 --> 08:40.770
On the other side
with a red tag.

08:40.854 --> 08:42.063
Okay. Great. Thank you.

08:42.147 --> 08:44.691
-Uh, we'll be fast, I promise.
-Thank you.

08:46.151 --> 08:48.236
This is a little trick
my mom taught me

08:48.319 --> 08:49.904
after the divorce.

08:49.988 --> 08:52.115
Money was tight,
so we used to go thrifting.

08:52.198 --> 08:54.325
You never told me that.

08:54.409 --> 08:57.871
Um... Yeah, well,
it's not exactly something

08:57.954 --> 09:00.373
-that you go around
bragging about, you know.
-KEVIN: Mm.

09:02.792 --> 09:04.377
Come on, start looking.

09:04.461 --> 09:07.464
Oh. Yes, ma'am. Yes, ma'am.

09:13.970 --> 09:16.389
Um, how are...
how are your kids doing?

09:17.432 --> 09:20.060
Oh, uh, they're incredible.

09:20.143 --> 09:21.853
They're incredible.
And I know that's something

09:21.936 --> 09:25.273
that all parents say, you know,
that their kids are special.

09:25.357 --> 09:26.775
My kids are special.

09:26.858 --> 09:28.735
They really are, though.
They... They're special.

09:28.818 --> 09:30.945
And they're so different.
They're so different.

09:31.029 --> 09:33.531
Franny is this, um,
really precocious little girl.

09:33.615 --> 09:35.700
She's always asking questions.
She's very curious.

09:35.784 --> 09:39.204
And Nicky is this, uh...
a wild child

09:39.287 --> 09:41.289
who dives into things headfirst

09:41.373 --> 09:43.500
without even thinking.
Sometimes literally.

09:43.583 --> 09:46.252
-Hmm. Sounds familiar.
-Yes.

09:46.336 --> 09:49.589
-Karma. It's a five-year-old
running with scissors.
-(Sophie laughs)

09:52.050 --> 09:53.551
(exhales)

09:53.635 --> 09:55.512
Oh, this might work.

09:57.764 --> 09:59.891
Oh, yeah.

09:59.974 --> 10:01.810
And I think that we passed
a dressing room

10:01.893 --> 10:03.478
-right there. Yeah.
-Oh, great.

10:09.109 --> 10:12.320
Um, can you, uh, hold this up
'cause it's...?

10:12.404 --> 10:14.322
Oh, yeah, sure.

10:14.406 --> 10:16.282
-No problem.
-SOPHIE: Thank you.

10:16.366 --> 10:17.951
You got it.

10:21.287 --> 10:22.789
SOPHIE (chuckles):
Oh, hey, I, uh...

10:22.872 --> 10:25.834
I recently saw a picture of you
in some magazine

10:25.917 --> 10:28.044
looking like one
of the Village People.

10:28.128 --> 10:30.797
Oh, yeah, that, um...
(chuckles)

10:30.880 --> 10:32.632
That was the <i>GQ</i> profile.

10:32.716 --> 10:34.175
I was trying to get press
for the nonprofit,

10:34.259 --> 10:35.969
and they insisted
that I wear a hard hat,

10:36.052 --> 10:38.805
so that's, uh, what that was.

10:38.888 --> 10:41.850
SOPHIE:
Oh. Well, it made me smile.

10:41.933 --> 10:43.977
At least it was
for a good cause.

10:44.060 --> 10:45.812
Okay,
you can let down the curtain.

10:45.895 --> 10:47.022
-KEVIN: Yeah?
-SOPHIE: Mm-hmm.

10:47.105 --> 10:48.690
-All right.
-(Sophie clears throat softly)

10:51.693 --> 10:53.611
(Sophie exhales)

10:55.613 --> 10:58.116
Yeah, this'll do.

10:58.199 --> 10:59.659
Yeah.

10:59.743 --> 11:02.370
I-I think
you'll get by just fine.

11:05.457 --> 11:06.708
So, yeah,
at first we weren't sure

11:06.791 --> 11:08.168
there'd be any interest,
but there's actually a...

11:08.251 --> 11:09.586
There's a big demand for it.

11:09.669 --> 11:11.796
These vets, they want...
they want connection, you know?

11:11.880 --> 11:13.131
They want community.

11:13.214 --> 11:15.508
Actually, this guy Hank,

11:15.592 --> 11:17.302
at a foundation pour last week,

11:17.385 --> 11:19.637
he tells me that working outside
with vets just like him

11:19.721 --> 11:21.598
gave him these little--
get this--

11:21.681 --> 11:24.100
pockets of peace.

11:24.184 --> 11:25.935
-Oh.
-Yeah. Peace that he said

11:26.019 --> 11:27.520
he didn't think
he'd ever be able to find.

11:27.604 --> 11:30.148
-Aw. Pockets of peace.
-Mm-hmm.

11:30.231 --> 11:32.901
-I love that.
-Me, too.

11:34.944 --> 11:36.821
So, how's saving lives
in the big city?

11:36.905 --> 11:38.823
-How's that going?
-Um, you know what?

11:38.907 --> 11:40.116
I'm actually saving lives

11:40.200 --> 11:43.078
outside a little town in Berlin
at the moment.

11:43.161 --> 11:45.663
Is that the-the German Berlin?

11:45.747 --> 11:47.791
Because I know there's, uh,
there's a Paris, Texas.

11:47.874 --> 11:51.378
-Uh, yeah, no. No,
it's the German one. (laughs)
-Okay.

11:51.461 --> 11:54.798
I'm-I'm working
as a traveling nurse now.

11:54.881 --> 11:57.801
-I didn't know that was a thing.
-Yeah. Yeah.

11:57.884 --> 12:00.011
Um, after my mom died,

12:00.095 --> 12:02.389
-I found this list
that she wrote.
-Uh-huh.

12:02.472 --> 12:06.643
Um, it was all these places
that she wanted to visit.

12:06.726 --> 12:08.311
So I made my own list.

12:08.395 --> 12:09.854
And we went

12:09.938 --> 12:12.941
-to Italy for our honeymoon.
-Mm-hmm.

12:13.024 --> 12:15.527
And then Paris.

12:15.610 --> 12:17.862
-You know, the French one.
-Wait, hold on a second.

12:17.946 --> 12:19.239
Did you say
that there's a French one?

12:19.322 --> 12:20.532
-There's a French one.
-Oh.

12:20.615 --> 12:22.117
-(chuckles)
-(imitates explosion)

12:22.200 --> 12:25.412
Yeah. And then my friend told me
about this traveling nurse gig,

12:25.495 --> 12:28.456
-so I just jumped
on the opportunity.
-Sounds like fun.

12:28.540 --> 12:29.916
It's got to be tough, though,
all that long distance

12:30.000 --> 12:31.167
with you and Grant, right?
I mean, that can't be...

12:31.251 --> 12:33.670
Oh, yeah, it is, but, um,

12:33.753 --> 12:36.798
you know, I can work
for a chunk and then,

12:36.881 --> 12:38.842
you know,
take a stretch off and...

12:38.925 --> 12:40.468
-Yeah.
-Yeah.

12:40.552 --> 12:43.680
I will admit, the, uh,
the red-eyes are killing me.

12:43.763 --> 12:46.349
-Yeah?
-Yeah. I'm getting old.

12:46.433 --> 12:49.352
-You're getting old?
I'm getting old.
-Oh, please.

12:49.436 --> 12:51.646
Kevin Pearson doesn't age.

12:51.730 --> 12:54.399
Kevin Pearson ages.
My beard's coming in gray.

12:54.482 --> 12:56.317
-No, it's not.
-It is, it is.
I'm thinking about dyeing it.

12:56.401 --> 12:58.028
-Right here on the corner.
Check it out. Look at...
-I don't believe you.

12:58.111 --> 12:59.487
-Get in there. Take a look.
-Let me see. Let me see.

12:59.571 --> 13:00.905
(gasps)
Oh, my God.

13:00.989 --> 13:03.158
-Yeah.
-You have gray hair.

13:03.241 --> 13:04.659
You are not allowed to dye that.

13:04.743 --> 13:05.869
I said I was thinking
about dyeing it.

