32:54.140 --> 32:56.559
Ladies and gentlemen,
thank you for gathering today.

32:56.643 --> 33:00.063
We've come together
to celebrate Kate and Philip.

33:00.146 --> 33:05.694
But the older we get, the faster
time just seems to come at us.

33:05.777 --> 33:07.696
That doesn't mean
there aren't still

33:07.779 --> 33:11.074
summer vacations to be enjoyed.

33:11.157 --> 33:15.036
There's still love to be shared.

33:15.120 --> 33:18.248
It just all happens much faster.

33:18.331 --> 33:20.250
(singing inaudibly)

33:20.333 --> 33:22.335
♪ ♪

33:29.426 --> 33:31.386
(indistinct chatter)

33:31.469 --> 33:34.222
♪ <i>Well, my friends,</i>
<i>the time has come</i> ♪

33:35.265 --> 33:38.101
♪ <i>To raise the roof</i>
<i>and have some fun...</i> ♪

33:38.184 --> 33:40.437
-RANDALL: Yo.
-Hey.

33:40.520 --> 33:42.689
So, for real, bro.

33:42.772 --> 33:44.649
What happened with you
last night?

33:45.692 --> 33:47.861
Oh, last night--
It was a long story.

33:47.944 --> 33:50.405
-Is it a good story?
-Uh...

33:50.488 --> 33:52.073
I don't know yet.

33:52.157 --> 33:53.533
Um...

33:55.535 --> 33:57.620
Sophie's no longer married.

33:57.704 --> 33:59.539
She's a single woman.

33:59.622 --> 34:02.334
-Manny say what?
-BETH: I knew it.

34:02.417 --> 34:04.544
I knew it.
This cracks the case wide open.

34:04.627 --> 34:06.963
-(taps wall)
-I got to go find Madison.

34:09.049 --> 34:11.009
-♪ <i>All night long</i> ♪
-♪ <i>All night</i> ♪

34:11.092 --> 34:12.594
-♪ <i>All night</i> ♪
-♪ <i>All night</i> ♪

34:12.677 --> 34:15.013
-♪ <i>All night long</i> ♪
-♪ <i>All night</i> ♪

34:15.096 --> 34:16.431
Oh, Rebecca.

34:16.514 --> 34:18.433
♪ <i>All night long...</i> ♪

34:18.516 --> 34:21.061
Your song was so beautiful.

34:21.144 --> 34:24.481
Thank you, sweetheart.

34:24.564 --> 34:26.775
Are you okay?

34:29.069 --> 34:30.987
(sighs)

34:31.071 --> 34:32.280
(tongue clicks)

34:38.036 --> 34:39.662
(sighs)

34:41.664 --> 34:43.667
It's Kevin, isn't it?

34:46.419 --> 34:50.256
I love my son,
but he is an idiot.

34:51.758 --> 34:54.803
-(both laugh)
-He is.

34:54.886 --> 34:59.182
I mean, he is 20 years old,
he's supposed to be, but...

35:01.518 --> 35:03.812
The timing is just off
right now.

35:05.480 --> 35:07.482
He isn't ready for you.

35:10.318 --> 35:12.612
He will be, but...

35:14.614 --> 35:17.951
...it's gonna take a while.

35:18.034 --> 35:22.622
And I don't know if you can
wait around for that.

35:22.706 --> 35:25.959
I mean, personally,
I don't know if I could.

35:26.042 --> 35:27.460
(exhales)

35:30.755 --> 35:33.591
But when the timing is right...

35:35.969 --> 35:38.221
...he's gonna be so great.

35:43.018 --> 35:44.644
Yeah.

35:48.356 --> 35:50.567
Wow, that's a lot, man.

35:50.650 --> 35:52.777
-Really is.
-Yeah.

35:52.861 --> 35:55.905
So, let me
get this straight. Um...

35:55.989 --> 35:59.200
the woman you've pined after
for years is finally single,

35:59.284 --> 36:01.411
and you're depressed about it?

36:02.829 --> 36:05.415
(exhales)
Just-- I don't want to...

36:05.498 --> 36:07.250
I don't want
to mess it up again.

36:07.334 --> 36:09.336
That's not gonna
happen, Captain.

36:09.419 --> 36:11.838
S-- Every time
we see each other,

36:11.921 --> 36:13.840
we blow up each other's
lives, it's-it's...

36:13.923 --> 36:16.092
I don't want
to do that, I don't...

36:16.176 --> 36:18.762
don't want to hurt her again.

36:18.845 --> 36:20.055
Huh.

36:22.515 --> 36:24.267
What are you doing?
What are you thinking?

36:24.351 --> 36:26.853
-I'm thinking about
the right thing to say here.
-Okay.

36:26.936 --> 36:28.355
I feel like you're at a moment
in life where you need

36:28.438 --> 36:30.440
really smart,
really sound advice.

36:30.523 --> 36:32.942
-Yes. Yes, please.
-Yeah. Okay. Yep.

36:33.026 --> 36:35.195
Okay, so this is...

36:35.278 --> 36:37.655
-This is what I got.
-Okay.

36:37.739 --> 36:39.657
Buffalo Bills
lost the Super Bowl

36:39.741 --> 36:42.160
four years in a row
when we were kids.

36:42.243 --> 36:44.245
-You remember that? Yeah.
-I do.

36:46.414 --> 36:48.416
-I'm not the Buffalo Bills.
-That's not what I'm saying.

36:48.500 --> 36:50.460
-Okay.
-Anyway, before
every Super Bowl,

36:50.543 --> 36:53.505
they make Super Bowl champion
merch with both teams on it

36:53.588 --> 36:55.965
so they have stuff ready
to go no matter who wins, right?

36:56.049 --> 36:58.176
-Mm-hmm.
-But once a team loses,

36:58.259 --> 37:01.179
they don't want the stuff
with the losing team on it.

37:01.262 --> 37:03.056
They don't want
"Super Bowl champion

37:03.139 --> 37:06.267
-Buffalo Bills" sweatshirts.
-Hmm.

37:06.351 --> 37:09.479
So, do you know
where that stuff used to go?

37:10.689 --> 37:12.023
I bet you're gonna tell me.

37:12.107 --> 37:13.191
-Other continents.
-Yeah?

37:13.274 --> 37:14.651
Africa. Asia.

37:14.734 --> 37:17.153
-Any and every nation in need.
-Huh.

37:17.237 --> 37:19.364
So, for four consecutive years
in the early '90s,

37:19.447 --> 37:22.033
there were world champion
Buffalo Bills merch

37:22.117 --> 37:24.327
flooding other continents.

37:24.411 --> 37:25.829
I-I don't know
where you're going...

37:25.912 --> 37:28.623
Kev, there are
tens of thousands of people

37:28.707 --> 37:30.291
who grew up thinking
that the Buffalo Bills

37:30.375 --> 37:33.920
were the greatest team
of all time.

37:34.004 --> 37:38.466
-The world
is friggin' insane, man.
-(laughs)

37:38.550 --> 37:41.594
It makes no sense.

37:41.678 --> 37:45.348
But you and Sophie together,

37:45.432 --> 37:48.977
now, that makes more sense
than most things.

37:49.060 --> 37:50.895
Hey.

37:50.979 --> 37:53.064
You're not gonna
screw it up this time.

37:54.149 --> 37:55.775
I know it.

38:00.238 --> 38:02.157
Thank you.

38:02.240 --> 38:04.242
♪ ♪

38:13.418 --> 38:15.879
-Hey.
-SOPHIE: Hi.

38:15.962 --> 38:17.088
-Talk to you?
-Yeah.

38:17.172 --> 38:19.090
-Yeah? Okay.
-Yes, sure.

38:19.174 --> 38:21.343
-Yes. Um...
-Uh...

38:21.426 --> 38:24.095
-Listen...
-I was actually gonna
come over and...

38:24.179 --> 38:26.473
I-I don't, I don't want you
to be a ball

38:26.556 --> 38:29.684
that I just bounce off of
to get to another ball.

38:29.768 --> 38:33.271
-What? Wait, just stop. I...
-I...

38:33.355 --> 38:35.940
Listen, y-you don't get
to give a speech this time.

38:36.024 --> 38:37.650
Okay? It-It's my turn.

38:39.361 --> 38:40.570
Okay.

38:42.947 --> 38:47.035
Look, I-I have spent
years of my life

38:47.118 --> 38:50.330
praying that you would...
(laughs) you would grow up.

38:53.875 --> 38:55.502
But...

38:56.544 --> 39:00.548
Now here you are,
20 years later...

39:02.550 --> 39:04.511
...and you're finally the man
that I always knew

39:04.594 --> 39:06.096
you possibly could be.

39:06.179 --> 39:09.224
♪ <i>How did it feel to be alone?</i> ♪

39:09.307 --> 39:11.685
At first, I-- honestly,
I didn't believe it,

39:11.768 --> 39:15.271
that we could finally be in the
right place at the right time.

39:15.355 --> 39:17.816
♪ <i>I was always thinking</i>
<i>of games...</i> ♪

39:17.899 --> 39:19.442
You know?

39:19.526 --> 39:23.571
And that I would finally be
the best version of myself.

39:23.655 --> 39:25.990
♪ <i>The best of my time...</i> ♪

39:26.074 --> 39:28.827
But I am.

39:28.910 --> 39:30.537
And you are.

39:32.247 --> 39:36.001
And... I don't know,
I freaked out.

39:36.084 --> 39:37.627
I freaked out last night
because I just don't,

39:37.711 --> 39:40.088
I don't want us to fall back

39:40.171 --> 39:44.134
into the old versions
of ourselves.

39:44.217 --> 39:46.845
-You know?
-Mm.

39:46.928 --> 39:51.725
I need you to love me
for the woman that I am now,

39:51.808 --> 39:53.518
not the woman that I was.

39:55.645 --> 39:57.856
'Cause you're not the man
that you were.

40:00.275 --> 40:02.861
And I want to fall in love
with the man that you've become.

40:02.944 --> 40:06.656
♪ <i>I have a friend I've...</i> ♪

40:06.740 --> 40:08.450
That was a ram--
that was a ramble.

40:08.533 --> 40:11.411
-I rambled.
-No.

40:11.494 --> 40:12.912
What were you gonna say?

40:16.916 --> 40:21.463
Well, I-I think in lieu of
you not wanting to repeat

40:21.546 --> 40:23.381
the patterns of the past,
I think it's-it's better if I...

40:23.465 --> 40:25.717
No, just say it.

40:25.800 --> 40:27.469
-Okay, again, I think,
in lieu of you...
-Stop saying

40:27.552 --> 40:29.721
"in lieu of," you're not even
using the word correctly.

40:29.804 --> 40:31.473
-Really?
-Yeah.

40:31.556 --> 40:34.059
(laughs):
Wha-What were you gonna say?

40:34.142 --> 40:37.228
♪ <i>Love can break your heart</i> ♪

40:37.312 --> 40:38.772
(exhales)

40:38.855 --> 40:42.400
♪ <i>Try to be sure</i> ♪

40:42.484 --> 40:46.613
♪ <i>Right from the start</i> ♪

40:46.696 --> 40:49.616
♪ <i>Yes, only love</i> ♪

